summary: A surge in hepatitis C tests is being driven by concerns over the infected blood scandal, with women in particular facing dismissal of their symptoms. The scandal involves thousands of people who were infected with HIV and Hepatitis C through contaminated blood products in the 1970s and 1980s. A doctor involved has described it as the "worst thing you can imagine." Amidst the scandal, the U.K. is allocating billions in compensation to victims. Additionally, research is ongoing to determine prevalent hepatitis C virus subtypes in Pakistan. The symptoms of hepatitis C, including early signs, are being highlighted, emphasizing the importance of timely GP consultation. Campaigners have voiced their concerns over the delayed recognition and inadequate support for victims, feeling "gas-lit for generations."

name: The Substance movie Demi Moore
summary: At the Cannes Film Festival, "The Substance," a body horror film, received a standing ovation for nine minutes. Demi Moore stars in the film, which critics have praised as both gruesome and hilarious. The film explores feminist themes and takes the concept of cosmetic enhancement to extremes. The reviews are largely positive, with many praising Moore's performance as her best in decades and calling the film "magnificently tasteless" and "visionary." Some believe it could earn Oscar recognition. Moore has addressed the film's extreme nudity and violence, stating that she hopes it will spark conversations about the pressures women face regarding their bodies. The film's reception has been overwhelmingly positive, with Variety reporting an 11-minute standing ovation at its premiere.

name: FA Cup
summary: BBC Sport has secured a deal with TNT Sports to continue providing free-to-air coverage of the Emirates FA Cup. The FA Cup final in 2024 will be played at Wembley Stadium, and it will be televised on both BBC Sport and TNT Sports. The match is scheduled to kick off at 3:00 PM GMT on May 11, 2024. Fans can also follow the match live on BBC Radio 5 Live and the BBC Sport website. Manchester City goalkeeper Ederson will miss the final two games of the season due to a fractured eye socket sustained in training. The FA Cup final will be a rematch of the 2023 final, which Manchester United won 2-1.

summary: Andy Murray has made a promising return to tennis after an ankle injury, progressing to the second round of the Geneva Open. He has announced upcoming tournaments as Wimbledon preparation, despite nearly facing defeat in Geneva before a storm halted play. Murray is making significant changes ahead of his retirement, switching to Yonex rackets after 20 years. Despite a victory in his first match back in Bordeaux, a recent loss in the Bordeaux Challenger event has raised concerns about his French Open preparations. Murray's performance has been closely observed by fellow British player Jack Draper, who anticipates guidance from the veteran as he prepares for the end of Murray's career.

name: Julian Assange
summary: Julian Assange, the founder of WikiLeaks, is facing legal challenges related to his extradition to the United States. The High Court in the United Kingdom has recently granted Assange the right to appeal the decision to extradite him to the US, where he is facing charges of violating espionage laws. The extradition process has garnered significant attention and has raised concerns over media freedom and the potential impact on journalism. Assange's supporters argue that his extradition would set a dangerous precedent, while the US authorities maintain that he must be held accountable for his alleged actions. The outcome of the appeal will have significant implications for Assange and the future of media accountability.
